courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of this course, students will be able to:

1. develop multiple approaches and empirical methods for the study of imperial capitals of Chang’an, Luoyang and Kaifeng and their metropolitan areas;

2. . master the basic concepts and knowledge of the imperial capital system with a focus on the ecology, morphology, city planning, socio-economic structure, military defense and metropolitan system;

3. comprehend the evolution of imperial capitals and the transformation of a dual capital system into a multiple capital system from the ancient time through the pre-modern period;

4. understand the structural transformation and eastward relocation trend of the national capital in North China during this period and the determining factors;

5. nurture comparative, critical and analytical thinking on various aspects of the imperial capital system, evaluating how far the evidence or examples in primary sources illustrate particular aspect(s) of the system, and whether they substantiate historians' claims;

6. write logical, coherent and creative term papers on particular aspect(s) of the imperial capital system based on various historical materials including historic monuments;

7. acquire skills of finding and interpreting relevant primary texts, communicating and collaborating with classmates, using appropriate reference tools and making written and oral presentations through term paper writing and interactive tutorials.

學生完成本課程後，將能：

1. 養成研習中國帝都長安、洛陽、開封及其畿內的歷史的多元視野和實證方法；

2. 學會有關中國帝都體制的基本概念和知識，尤其明瞭帝都的生態環境、形態結構、城市規劃、社會經濟結構、軍事防衛及畿內制度等；

3. 理解從古代至近世期間中國帝都的演進以及兩都制轉型為數都制的發展；

4. 明瞭古代至近世期間帝國首都的結構性轉變、在北中國向東遷移的趨勢以及相關的因素；

5. 養成探究帝都體制各方面的比較視野和批判分析思維，例如能評估原始文獻中有關證據或事例在多少程度上說明帝都體制的某(些)方面，或檢查諸載例能否證明史家的論點；

6. 就帝都體制的某(些)方面，根據各種歷史資料包括歷史遺跡，撰寫具邏輯、連貫性及創意的論文；

7. 透過學期論文指導和互動性導修，掌握搜尋和詮釋相關原始文獻、跟其他同學溝通協作、運用合適參考工具及進行書面和口頭報告等技巧。

By the end of the course, students will:

•Have enhanced awareness and curiosity of the complex issue of cultural difference, political change, and international relationship in early modern East Asia;
•Have enhanced sensitivity towards discourse, narratives, values and hidden agenda in historical records;
•Have enhanced ability to practice the science and art of historical research;
•Have enhanced reading, writing, and oral expression skills.

修讀本課程之後，學生將得到以下學習成果：
\*增加對於近代東亞的文化差異、政治變遷、國際關係的認識及興趣;
\*更準確和敏感地把握歷史檔案中的話語、敘述、價值及隱含之動機；

\*改善歷史研究這門科學和藝術的技藝；

\*改善閱讀、寫作、口頭表達與辯論的技巧。
